25/01/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- The second three-day phase of intensified talks on the reunification of Cyprus begins on Monday (January 25th).
The first phase took place from January 11-13th.
It focused on governance and power sharing.
This second round between Cypriot President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat will cover that issue and will also touch on EU-related issues and the economy.
(Phileleftheros, Financial Mirror - 25/01/10)
